  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">What are <span>scleral lenses</span>?</h2>
      <div class="que-son-inner">
        <div class="que-son-texto">
          <p>Scleral lenses are large-diameter rigid gas-permeable contact lenses that vault completely over the cornea and rest on the sclera (the white of the eye). This design creates a fluid reservoir between the lens and the cornea.</p>
          <p>Unlike conventional contact lenses, sclerals are ideal for irregular or damaged corneas where soft or standard rigid lenses fail to provide adequate vision or comfort.</p>
          <p>The result is crisp, stable, comfortable vision even in the most complex cases — including advanced keratoconus, post-transplant corneas, and severe dry eye.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="stats-grid">
            <div class="stat">
              <strong>+10</strong>
              <span>years of specialty</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <strong>98%</strong>
              <span>fitting success rate</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <strong>&lt;30</strong>
              <span>min from San Diego border</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <strong>EN</strong>
              <span>English-speaking team</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Conditions we <span>treat</span></h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Scleral lenses are the treatment of choice for various complex corneal conditions.</p>
      <div class="condiciones">
        <div class="condicion">
          <span class="condicion-icon">🔺</span>
          <h4>Keratoconus</h4>
          <p>Progressive cone-shaped corneal deformation that prevents clear vision with conventional lenses. Scleral lenses vault over the cone and deliver sharp vision regardless of severity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="condicion">
          <span class="condicion-icon">🔬</span>
          <h4>Corneal transplant</h4>
          <p>Optimal visual recovery post-transplant by compensating for graft irregularity. Many patients achieve 20/20 vision that they couldn't reach with glasses.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="condicion">
          <span class="condicion-icon">⚡</span>
          <h4>Post-refractive surgery</h4>
          <p>For patients unsatisfied with LASIK, PRK, or radial keratotomy results. Scleral lenses neutralize the irregular corneal surface left behind.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="condicion">
          <span class="condicion-icon">💧</span>
          <h4>Severe dry eye</h4>
          <p>The saline reservoir in scleral lenses bathes the corneal surface throughout the day — providing relief that eye drops alone cannot maintain.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="condicion">
          <span class="condicion-icon">🌐</span>
          <h4>Pellucid marginal degeneration</h4>
          <p>A variant of corneal ectasia affecting the lower corneal periphery. Scleral lenses are often the only optical option for functional vision.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="condicion">
          <span class="condicion-icon">👁️</span>
          <h4>Other irregular corneas</h4>
          <p>Trauma, chemical burns, Steven-Johnson syndrome, aniridia, and other causes of corneal irregularity benefit from scleral lens correction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

