          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            How long do scleral lenses last?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" role="region">
            <p>With proper care and cleaning, scleral lenses typically last 1 to 3 years. Their lifespan depends on how well they are maintained and whether your corneal prescription remains stable. We provide complete care instructions and a cleaning kit at the time of fitting.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            Can I wear scleral lenses if I've had LASIK or another refractive surgery?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" role="region">
            <p>Yes. In fact, post-refractive surgery patients are among the most common candidates for scleral lenses. If you are unhappy with your LASIK, PRK, or radial keratotomy results, scleral lenses can neutralize the corneal irregularity and restore the clear vision you were hoping to achieve with surgery.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

